items.name: Hugo
items.tagline: The AI Agent that doesn't charge 1$ per support ticket
items.description: Hugo is an AI agent built to offload companies from repetitive support queries. It resolves conversations and automates tasks end-to-end, safely. Built by the team behind Crisp, Hugo brings production-grade AI support to any business, without fragile workflows or per-resolution fees.

items.name: Atoms
items.tagline: Turn your ideas into products that sell
items.description: Atoms is a vibe business team that turns your ideas into business. It researches your market, designs the product, builds frontend and backend, connects auth and payments, and ships a live app you can charge for, not just a prototype

items.name: findable.
items.tagline: A full Answer Engine Optimization (AEO) platform for free
items.description: findable is a full Answer Engine Optimization (AEO) platform for unlocking ChatGPT, Google Gemini, Google AI Mode, Meta AI, Grok, Perplexity and co for marketing and sales. With findable free we have now added a comprehensive free plan that includes everything you need to get started with Answer Engine Optimization.

items.name: Codex by OpenAI
items.tagline: A command center for working with agents
items.description: Introducing the Codex app for macOS‚Äîa command center for AI coding and software development with multiple agents, parallel workflows, and long-running tasks. The Codex app changes how software gets built and who can build it‚Äîfrom pairing with a single coding agent on targeted edits to supervising coordinated teams of agents across the full lifecycle of designing, building, shipping, and maintaining software.

items.name: Helply
items.tagline: 65% AI resolution rate in 90 days, or you pay nothing
items.description: Helply is an AI support agent that resolves support conversations end-to-end, takes real actions, syncs to your help desk, and escalates with full context and source citations. Work 1-on-1 with a dedicated AI support engineer and get a 65% AI resolution rate in 90 days, or you pay nothing.

items.name: AI Doc Writer by Trupeer
items.tagline: Create finished, on-brand docs from simple recordings.
items.description: Turn raw recordings (walkthroughs, internal processes, demos, zoom calls) into finished step-by-step docs in minutes. Trupeer understands what‚Äôs on screen, picks the actions that matter, and generates a structured guide with clear summary, steps and relevant screenshots. Upload a sample guide to learn your structure, tone, fonts and logos so every doc stays on brand. Vision-based analysis works even on imperfect or old recordings.

items.name: Relay.app Agents
items.tagline: Build an AI team that works for you
items.description: Relay.app the easiest way to create a team of AI agents that work for you across Gmail, Notion, HubSpot and hundreds of other apps. Relay.app agents work for you proactively day and night and get better over time.

items.name: Lightfern for Email
items.description: Finish thoughts before fingers hit keys. Working directly in your inbox as a browser extension, Lightfern nails the details that make emails feel like you - nicknames, sign-offs, your tone of voice - and pulls context from past threads to finish sentences the way you would. All with zero data retention by default.

items.name: Grok Imagine 1.0
items.tagline: It‚Äôs never been easier to bring your ideas to life.
items.description: xAI launches Grok Imagine 1.0, a major upgrade to its AI video generation platform. The release improves video quality, latency, and cost efficiency, supports up to 10s 720p videos with better audio, and adds advanced motion and visual continuity. A new unified API enables end-to-end video creation and editing from text, images, or existing footage.

items.name: Logo Link by Brand.dev
items.tagline: Display any company logo with a single URL. No API needed.
items.description: Brand.dev is a brand data API used by 5,000+ companies. Our customers kept asking for a simpler way to display logos in client-facing UIs without the overhead of API calls. Logo Link is the answer, optimized for high-volume reads via a global CDN.
